title: 5 Seconds of Summer Releases 'Hey Everybody' Video, Tour Schedule
text:
Comments The pop punk band's members imagine themselves as rich people in bathrobe, living with a butler in a huge mansion. 
Former YouTube sensations 5 Seconds of Summer is back with a new music video for "Hey Everybody". A tribute for the underpaid and the overworked, the video shows the quartet fantasizing about living as rich people with money just thrown at them and raked like leaves. The video is directed by Isaac Rentz who also helmed the band's "She's Kinda Hot", "Good Girls", "Amnesia" and "Don't Stop" videos. Michael Clifford takes a job in hot dog costume, Ashton Irwin entertains children as dinosaur, Calum Hood walks multiple dogs and Luke Hemmings gets stuck in an internship. "Hey Everybody" is a single from their sophomore album " Sounds Good Feels Good " which is set for release on October 23. The song samples "Hungry Like the Wolf" by Duran Duran . In addition to the video, the band announced "Sounds Live Feels Live" tour which kicks off July 2016 in Uncasville, CT. The band is also among the line-up of this year's iHeartRadio Jingle Ball 2015 Tour that kicks off December 1.
